<title>BRAZIL: Brazil to fund staff reductions at key ports.</title>
<headline>Brazil to fund staff reductions at key ports.</headline>
<dateline>BRASILIA 1997-08-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Brazilian government will pump 134 million reais into the port authorities at Rio de Janeiro and Santos to fund staff reduction programs, said Planning Minister Antonio Kandir Thursday.</p>
<p>After a meeting of the National Privatization Council (CND), Kandir said the government would free up 44 million reais for Companhia Docas do Rio and 90 million reais for the Santos port authority, CODESP.</p>
<p>Kandir said the privatization of port services in Brazil was progressing well.</p>
<p>The privatization council plans to auction a concession to run the Santos container port on September 17, with a minimum price of 101.184 million reais.</p>
<p>((-- Michael Christie, Brasilia newsroom 55-61-3141193))</p>
